---
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Affiliate Disclosure — CodeStackHub',
  description: 'How CodeStackHub earns from affiliate links and ads, and our commitment to honest, independent recommendations.',
  robots: { index: true, follow: true },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 mx-auto lg:px-8 lg:py-20 max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="font-bold font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl leading-tighter tracking-tighter mb-4">
      Affiliate Disclosure
    </h1>
    <p class="text-muted mb-8">
      Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        CodeStackHub is a participant in affiliate advertising programs designed to provide a
        means for us to earn fees by linking to retailer websites. When you click a link on this
        site and make a purchase, we may receive a commission — at no additional cost to you.
      </p>

      <h2>Programs We Participate In</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Amazon Associates Program:</strong> As an Amazon Associate, we earn from qualifying
          purchases. The commission we earn helps us keep this site free to use.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Other affiliate networks:</strong> ShareASale, Impact, Awin, and direct
          partnerships with sleep brands. All disclosed where applicable.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
      <p>
        Affiliate relationships <em>never</em> dictate which products we recommend. We test, compare,
        and review based on:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Published clinical research and sleep science</li>
        <li>Independent customer reviews and Reddit consensus</li>
        <li>Hands-on testing where feasible</li>
        <li>Transparent ingredient and spec analysis</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If a product underperforms, we say so — even if it pays a higher commission. If a non-affiliate
        product is the better choice, we recommend it anyway.
      </p>

      <h2>Pricing and Availability</h2>
      <p>
        Prices and availability shown on this site are accurate as of the date stated on each post,
        but they change. The retailer's checkout page is always the source of truth. We do not control
        third-party pricing.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        This site may display ads from networks like Google AdSense. Those networks may use cookies
        to serve ads based on your prior visits. You can opt out of personalized advertising by
        visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Content on CodeStackHub is for informational purposes only and is not medical advice.
        Always consult a qualified healthcare provider for sleep disorders, supplement interactions,
        or any health concern.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about how we earn or how we make recommendations, contact us via
        the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
